00:00:07.675 --> 00:00:09.636
and they give us some choices here.

00:00:09.636 --> 00:00:12.218
So let's just think a
little bit about this series

00:00:12.218 --> 00:00:13.323
that they gave us.

00:00:13.323 --> 00:00:14.634
So if we were to expand it out,

00:00:14.634 --> 00:00:16.761
let's see, when n is equal to zero,

00:00:16.761 --> 00:00:18.401
it'd be negative one to the zero power

00:00:18.401 --> 00:00:21.925
which is one times x to
the zero which is one

00:00:21.925 --> 00:00:23.945
over zero factorial which is one

00:00:23.945 --> 00:00:25.612
so it'll be one plus

00:00:26.883 --> 00:00:28.599
and then when n is one,

00:00:28.599 --> 00:00:30.338
well then this is going to be negative

00:00:30.338 --> 00:00:34.244
so it's going to be minus
and then x to the first

00:00:34.244 --> 00:00:36.244
over one factorial over,

00:00:37.136 --> 00:00:40.916
well, I could just write
that as x over here

00:00:40.916 --> 00:00:42.557
and then when n is two,

00:00:42.557 --> 00:00:44.679
the negative one squared,

00:00:44.679 --> 00:00:48.512
that's gonna be positive
x squared over two

00:00:49.385 --> 00:00:52.033
and there's going to
be minus x to the third

00:00:52.033 --> 00:00:54.324
over three factorial

00:00:54.324 --> 00:00:56.413
and then it's going to be
plus and I can keep going.

00:00:56.413 --> 00:00:57.804
You've seen this before.

00:00:57.804 --> 00:01:01.198
x to the fourth over four factorial

00:01:01.198 --> 00:01:02.509
and it's gonna keep going.

00:01:02.509 --> 00:01:03.892
Minus, plus.

00:01:03.892 --> 00:01:07.022
It's going to keep
alternating on and on and on.

00:01:07.022 --> 00:01:10.780
Now, our general form for
a Taylor series about zero

00:01:10.780 --> 00:01:14.095
which we could also call a
Maclaurin series would be,

00:01:14.095 --> 00:01:17.012
our general form would be f of zero

00:01:19.292 --> 00:01:21.625
plus f prime of zero times x

00:01:24.319 --> 00:01:26.486
plus f prime prime of zero

00:01:28.410 --> 00:01:30.660
times x squared over two

00:01:32.139 --> 00:01:35.609
plus the the third derivative at zero

00:01:35.609 --> 00:01:39.383
times x to the third over three factorial

00:01:39.383 --> 00:01:41.920
plus the fourth derivative,
you get the idea,

00:01:41.920 --> 00:01:46.136
evaluated at zero times x to
the fourth over four factorial

00:01:46.136 --> 00:01:48.637
and we would just go on and on and on.

00:01:48.637 --> 00:01:50.891
Now, to figure out which function,

00:01:50.891 --> 00:01:53.873
in order what I wrote in
blue to be the Maclaurin

00:01:53.873 --> 00:01:55.555
or to be the Taylor series about zero

00:01:55.555 --> 00:01:57.518
or in order to be the Maclaurin series,

00:01:57.518 --> 00:01:58.851
that means that,

00:01:59.970 --> 00:02:03.412
that means that f of zero
needs to be equal to one.

00:02:03.412 --> 00:02:06.069
It means that f prime of zero,

00:02:06.069 --> 00:02:07.744
actually let me write this down.

00:02:07.744 --> 00:02:11.222
It means that f of zero
needs to be equal to one.

00:02:11.222 --> 00:02:13.773
f of zero is equal to one.

00:02:13.773 --> 00:02:16.190
It means that f prime of zero

00:02:17.710 --> 00:02:19.592
needs to be the coefficient on the x here

00:02:19.592 --> 00:02:21.825
which is negative one

00:02:21.825 --> 00:02:22.781
and we could keep going.

00:02:22.781 --> 00:02:26.948
It means that, it means that
the second derivative at zero,

00:02:28.095 --> 00:02:29.331
well, that's going to be the coefficient

00:02:29.331 --> 00:02:31.247
on this x squared over two

00:02:31.247 --> 00:02:33.949
so that's gotta be equal to one

00:02:33.949 --> 00:02:35.356
and you see the general idea

00:02:35.356 --> 00:02:39.227
that the third derivative at
zero is equal to negative one.

00:02:39.227 --> 00:02:41.910
It's the coefficient on the x to the third

00:02:41.910 --> 00:02:45.119
over three factorial which is
negative one right over here.

00:02:45.119 --> 00:02:46.721
And so just using this information

00:02:46.721 --> 00:02:49.014
can we figure out which of these it is.

00:02:49.014 --> 00:02:51.823
So you could do a little bit
